n as the 'Onion Range', it was the highest barrier crossed by the ancient Silk Road connecting China and Central Asia."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","Blood-Sweating Horses"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-4-2","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"Then Suddenly Froze Amid the Flood of Men / Frozen into the Shape of a Blood-Sweating Horse, Neighing Skyward"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The gates of Dayuan opened at last"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Not to diplomacy, but to the sword"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Inside the walls, the fabled horses"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Stamped and snorted in their stalls"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Their flanks glistened with crimson moisture"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"As though they wept blood in the heat"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The soldiers stared"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"These were the horses the emperor dreamed of?"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Three thousand horses were led out"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Their hooves striking the stone road"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like a drumroll from the heart of the earth"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"One horse reared suddenly amid the flood of men"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Frozen into the shape of a blood-sweating horse"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Neighing at the sky"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"As though even it knew the price that had been paid"}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","Blood-Sweating Horses"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-4-3","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"Toward the Distant West / Toward the Unforgettable West"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The long march home"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Three thousand horses in a river of dust"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Through the Wuzi Bieli pass"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Through the iron-cold nights of the Pamir"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The horses of Dayuan, unaccustomed to this land"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Stumbled on the gravel of the Taklamakan"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Some fell and did not rise"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Their blood seeping into the sand"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"— Red as the sweat they once shed when they ran"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The soldiers sang no songs on this road"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"They had sung them all on the way out"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Now only the wind sang"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And the distant creaking of the supply carts"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Li Guangli counted the horses each dawn"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Each dawn the number was smaller"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"As though the desert were drinking them"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He thought of the Amu River"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Where the water was sweet and the grass was green"}],["$","p","22",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Where the Yuezhi people once grazed their flocks"}],["$","p","23",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Before Zhang Qian came, before anyone came"}],["$","p","24",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","25",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Toward the distant west"}],["$","p","26",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Toward the unforgettable west"}],["$","p","27",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He had traveled with the force of empire behind him"}],["$","p","28",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And now he returned"}],["$","p","29",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"With an empire's worth of grief ahead"}],["$","p","30",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","31",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"How many horses would survive to reach Chang'an?"}],["$","p","32",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"How many soldiers?"}],["$","p","33",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The blood-sweating horses of Dayuan"}],["$","p","34",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Had no answer"}],["$","p","35",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"They simply walked on"}],["$","p","36",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Toward the east"}],["$","p","37",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Their crimson sweat drying in the desert wind"}],["$","p","38",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like the last ink on a silk letter"}],["$","p","39",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That no one would read"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"text-xs font-sans font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4","children":"注释"}],["$","ol",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[1,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Taklamakan Desert"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Taklamakan Desert — China's largest desert, located in the Tarim Basin of Xinjiang. In Uyghur, it allegedly means 'place from which there is no return', spanning around 330,000 square kilometers."]}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"te