":"The solemn, gentle towers of Chang'an"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The emperor waits at the Xuanwu Gate"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"His ministers in their silken robes"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The incense burners sending blue spirals skyward"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of the three thousand blood-sweating horses"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Only a thousand have survived the road"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Their flanks still glistening"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But now more bone than muscle"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The emperor will compose his 'Song of the Heavenly Horses' —"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"'Their spirit is extraordinary, their power divine' —"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And have it performed with bells and jade chimes"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But Li Guangli will remember"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Not the bells"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But the sound of horses falling in the sand"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Not the jade chimes"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But the silence after the last soldier's cry"}],["$","p","22",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","23",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The blood-sweating horses of Dayuan"}],["$","p","24",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Now stand in the imperial stables"}],["$","p","25",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Their crimson sweat still beading"}],["$","p","26",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like the tears of every man who did not return"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"text-xs font-sans font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4","children":"注释"}],["$","ol",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[1,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Emperor Wu of Han"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Emperor Wu (Liu Che, 156–87 BC) — the seventh emperor of the Western Han. A visionary ruler who expanded the empire westward and dispatched Zhang Qian to open the Silk Road."]}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[2,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Song of the Heavenly Horses from the Western Extremity"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Song of the Heavenly Horses — a Yuefu poem composed personally by Emperor Wu of Han after obtaining the blood-sweating horses, praising their majestic spirit to express his grand imperial ambitions."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","Blood-Sweating Horses"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 tex