gation, his first major victory in the Western Regions.","children":["Shanshan",["$","sup",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 ml-px select-none","children":2}]]}],", the first test came"]}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The Xiongnu envoys had arrived before him"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Outnumbering his men ten to one"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That night he lit fires around the Xiongnu camp"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And his men roared like an army of thousands"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Drowning out even the thunderous hoofbeats"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like a storm descending"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"By dawn, the Xiongnu envoys were dead"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":["And the King of ",["$","span","1",{"className":"annotation-term border-b border-dotted border-gray-400 cursor-help","title":"Shanshan — a Silk Road kingdom (formerly Loulan); the site of Ban Chao's daring night raid on a Xiongnu delegation, his first major victory in the Western Regions.","children":["Shanshan",["$","sup",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 ml-px select-none","children":2}]]}]]}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Knelt before the Han flag"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":[["$","span","0",{"className":"annotation-term border-b border-dotted border-gray-400 cursor-help","title":"Ban Chao (32–102 AD) — a legendary Eastern Han general and diplomat who, with only 36 men, re-established Chinese suzerainty across the Western Regions over a 31-year campaign.","children":["Ban Chao",["$","sup",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 ml-px select-none","children":1}]]}]," smiled"]}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"As a scholar smiles"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"When the right character finally"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Falls into place"}],["$","p","22",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","23",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Thirty years he stayed in the western lands"}],["$","p","24",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Thirty years with thirty-six men"}],["$","p","25",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Who became an empire's shield"}],["$","p","26",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"At the edge of the world"}],["$","p","27",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","28",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The beacon-fires he lit"}],["$","p","29",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Along the old Silk Road"}],["$","p","30",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Burned for three decades"}],["$","p","31",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Then died, one by one"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"text-xs font-sans font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4","children":"注释"}],["$","ol",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[1,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Ban Chao"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Ban Chao (32–102 AD) — a legendary Eastern Han general and diplomat who, with only 36 men, re-established Chinese suzerainty across the Western Regions over a 31-year campaign."]}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"