oots"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Bitter seawater mingled with bitter tears"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Cast again into the dark-blue Persian Gulf"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He had come so far"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Across the Pamir's frozen passes"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Through the sands of the Taklamakan"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Past the ruins of kingdoms"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Whose names even scholars had forgotten"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And here, at the threshold of Rome"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He was turned back"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Not by an army"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But by a merchant's lie"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"'The sea will take two years,' they said"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Knowing it took only weeks"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Knowing that if East met West directly"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Their middleman's fortune would vanish"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Gan Ying turned east"}],["$","p","22",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"His shadow falling on the Persian Gulf"}],["$","p","23",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The longest shadow China ever cast westward"}],["$","p","24",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","25",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He carried back reports"}],["$","p","26",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of glass that could be blown like breath"}],["$","p","27",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of acrobats and fire-swallowers"}],["$","p","28",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of an empire that matched his own"}],["$","p","29",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","30",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Two empires, ignorant of each other"}],["$","p","31",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Separated by desert and deceit"}],["$","p","32",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And one man"}],["$","p","33",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Who almost — almost —"}],["$","p","34",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Bridged the distance"}],["$","p","35",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Standing ankle-deep"}],["$","p","36",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"In the dark-blue waves"}],["$","p","37",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of the Persian Gulf"}],["$","p","38",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"In the year 97 AD"}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","The Dark-Blue Persian Gulf"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","div","chapter-10",{"className":"mb-24 px-4","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-sans font-bold text-gray-300 uppercase tracking-widest pl-8 mb-8 border-l-4 border-gray-100","children":"Waves of the Tarim River"}],[["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-10-1","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"His Three Thousand Dunhuang Soldiers / Also Fell Prostrate on the Riverbank"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Suo Le led three thousand men from Dunhuang"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Across the burning Taklamakan"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":["To the banks of the ",["$","span","1",{"className":"annotation-term border-b border-dotted border-gray-400 cursor-help","title":"Tarim River — China's longest inland river, stretching about 2,137 kilometers along the northern edge of the Tarim Basin. Historically, the lifeblood of garrison agriculture in the Western Regions.","children":["Tarim River",["$","sup",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 ml-px select-none","children":1}]]}]]}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The river was their lifeline —"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Dark water rushing from the melting snows"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of mountains they could not see"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"His three thousand Dunhuang soldiers"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Also fell prostrate on the riverbank"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Pressing their faces to the water"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Drinking as though they would never drink again"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Then they rose and began to farm"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"These soldiers who had carried swords"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Now carried plows"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The first military farms of the Western Regions"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Planted in blood-soaked earth"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Irrigated by snowmelt"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Guarded by men who missed their homes"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","22",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"This was the beginning —"}],["$","p","23",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The ancestor of the bingtuan"}],["$","p","24",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The seed that would grow"}],["$","p","25",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Two thousand years later"}],["$","p","26",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Into the cities of the frontier"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"text-xs font-sans font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4","children":"注释"}],["$","ol",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[1,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Tarim River"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Tarim River — China's longest inland river, stretching about 2,137 kilometers along the northern edge of the Tarim Basin. Historically, the lifeblood of garrison agriculture in the Western Regions."]}]]}],["$","li","1",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[2,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Suo Mai"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Suo Mai — an Eastern Han general who led 3,000 troops from Dunhuang to forcibly cross the Tarim River, pioneering large-scale military agricultural colonies (tuntian) in the heart of the Western Regions."]}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[3,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Military Reclamation"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Military Reclamation — the system of using military troops to cultivate wasteland for agricultural production. Originating in the Han Dynasty's 'tuntian' policy in the Western Regions, it is the historical precedent for the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","Waves of the Tarim River"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-10-2","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"Eyes Gently Closed / A Green Cloud Drifts from the Distance"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Eyes gently closed"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A green cloud drifts from the distance"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"In his dream, the Tarim shore"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Is no longer barren"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Fields of wheat stretch to the horizon"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Canals thread through the desert"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like silver veins in stone"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He sees a future he cannot live to see"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A future of orchards and cotton"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of roads and schools"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of children who will never know"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The sound of sword on shield"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Eyes gently closed"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He farms in his dream"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The eternal farm"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The dream of every soldier"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Who wants peace more than glory"}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","Waves of the Tarim River"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{