k-Kul — a vast endorheic lake in the northern Tian Shan mountains in eastern Kyrgyzstan, the second-largest alpine lake in the world."]}]]}],["$","li","2",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[3,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Yabghu Qaghan"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Yabghu Qaghan — ruler of the Western Turkic Khaganate who warmly received Xuanzang in Central Asia, providing him with escorts and diplomatic credentials to continue his westward journey."]}]]}],["$","li","3",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[4,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Xuanzang"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Xuanzang (602–664) — a legendary Tang Dynasty Buddhist monk whose 17-year overland pilgrimage to India and meticulous geographic records inspired the classic novel 'Journey to the West'."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","The Mendicant Who Crossed the Border in Secret"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","div","chapter-12",{"className":"mb-24 px-4","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-sans font-bold text-gray-300 uppercase tracking-widest pl-8 mb-8 border-l-4 border-gray-100","children":"The Poet's Soul Still Gallops"}],[["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-12-1","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"O, No Longer a Solitary Pilgrim / A Warm Current Dispels the Bitter Cold"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Cen Can arrived at the frontier in autumn"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"When the first snow dusted the Tianshan"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"O, no longer a solitary pilgrim"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A warm current dispels the bitter cold"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"For here was a poet among soldiers"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A man of brushes amid men of swords"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Who saw beauty in the terrible:"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"'The north wind sweeps the earth, snapping white grasses,"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"In the eighth month, snow falls on the Tartar frontier —"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like a spring gale scattering blossoms of pear,'"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"His eyes drank the landscape"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That terrified other men:"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The thousand-league ice sheet"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The ten-thousand-league frozen cloud"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He saw them not as hardship"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But as grandeur"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Not as exile"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But as inspiration"}],["$","p","22",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","23",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"This was the poet of the frontier"}],["$","p","24",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Whose verses galloped like warhorses"}],["$","p","25",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Across the pages of Tang Dynasty literature"}],["$","p","26",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Cen Can — whose soul still gallops"}],["$","p","27",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Along the Silk Road"}],["$","p","28",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"In every line he wrote"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-gray-100","children":[["$","h4",null,{"className":"text-xs font-sans font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4","children":"注释"}],["$","ol",null,{"className":"space-y-2","children":[["$","li","0",{"className":"flex text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-xs text-gray-400 mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 font-mono","children":[1,"."]}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"font-medium text-gray-600","children":"Cen Shen"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-1.5 text-gray-300","children":"—"}],"Cen Shen (c. 715–770) — one of the greatest Tang Dynasty frontier poets, celebrated for his majestic, harsh, and vivid depictions of Silk Road landscapes and military campaigns."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","The Poet's Soul Still Gallops"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-12-2","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"With the Hand That Had Swung the Saber / He Hastily Caressed the Poem-Pouch at His Waist"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Between battles, he wrote"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"With the hand that had swung the saber"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He hastily caressed the poem-pouch at his waist"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That leather satchel where he kept his drafts"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Under the same stars"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That Zhang Qian had navigated by"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Under the same moon"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That Su Wu had wept beneath"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He dipped his brush in battlefield ink"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And wrote of snow and fire"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of homesickness and heroism"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of a land so beautiful and so brutal"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That only poetry could contain it"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Only verse could hold"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The contradictions of the frontier:"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Icicles on sword-blades"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Spring flowers on gravestones"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The cry of a northern flute"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"In the silence after slaughter"}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","The Poet's Soul Still Gallops"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-12-3","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"The Orange Campfire Still Gleams / A New Star Added to the Night Sky of Central Asia"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The orange campfire still gleams"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A new star added to the night sky of Central Asia"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Cen Can recites his verses to the soldiers"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Who listen with tears in their eyes"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"They had not known"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That their suffering could be beautiful"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That their exile could become legend"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"That a poet's brush could dignify"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Their frozen, bleeding hands"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The campfire crackles"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The horses stamp in the cold"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And somewhere in the dark beyond"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The mountains listen"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"As they have always listened"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"To the human voices at their feet"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The orange campfire still gleams"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Across twelve hundred years"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And will not die"}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","The Poet's Soul Still Gallops"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-12-4","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"So Still You Can Hear / The Poet's Teardrops Falling"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"When Cen Can left the frontier"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He looked back at the Tianshan"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"So still you can hear"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The poet's teardrops falling"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He had arrived fearing the wilderness"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He left loving it"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He had arrived a minor official"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He left a major poet"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The frontier had forged him"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"As fire forges steel"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The cold, the distance, the loneliness"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Had sharpened his verses"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Into diamond points"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"So still you can hear"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Even now"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The echo of his brush on paper"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"In the wind that blows"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Through the passes of the Tianshan"}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","The Poet's Soul Still Gallops"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}],["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-12-5","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"Like the Crimson Paper-Cut His Wife Made / On Their Wedding Night"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He dreamed of home"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of his wife's face in lamplight"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like the crimson paper-cut his wife made"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"On their wedding night"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Red as the desert sunset"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Delicate as frost on glass"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A pattern of paired birds"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Of intertwined branches"}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He folded the paper-cut"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And placed it in his poem-pouch"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Next to the verses"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Written in frontier snow"}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Even now"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"When you read his poems"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"You can feel"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The warmth of that paper-cut"}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Against the cold of the frontier"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Love pressed against distance"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Home carried in a leather satchel"}],["$","p","22",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Along the Silk Road"}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses","》 · ","The Poet's Soul Still Gallops"]}],"$undefined"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"mt-2 text-xs text-gray-400 text-center","children":["Li Yu"," / ","1995"]}]]}]]}]]]}],["$","div","chapter-13",{"className":"mb-24 px-4","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-sans font-bold text-gray-300 uppercase tracking-widest pl-8 mb-8 border-l-4 border-gray-100","children":"O, the Battle of Talas"}],[["$","article",null,{"id":"poem-13-1","className":"max-w-2xl mx-auto py-32 px-8 scroll-mt-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 font-serif leading-relaxed","children":"He Seems to See His Cavalry Charging / Along the Banks of the Talas River"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-1 font-serif text-xl text-gray-800 leading-[2.2]","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The Battle of Talas, 751 AD"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Where the Tang Empire met the Abbasid Caliphate"}],["$","p","2",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Where East met West in blood and fire"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","4",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"He seems to see his cavalry charging"}],["$","p","5",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Along the banks of the Talas River"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The last great push of Chinese power westward"}],["$","p","7",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Into the heartland of Islam"}],["$","p","8",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","9",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The battle was lost"}],["$","p","10",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The Tang armies broken"}],["$","p","11",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The frontier recoiled"}],["$","p","12",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Like a snapped bowstring"}],["$","p","13",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","14",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But from the prisoners of that battle"}],["$","p","15",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The secret of papermaking"}],["$","p","16",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Traveled west to Samarkand"}],["$","p","17",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"To Baghdad, to Cairo, to Europe"}],["$","p","18",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","19",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"And the world was changed forever"}],["$","p","20",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"Not by the victor's sword"}],["$","p","21",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"But by the captive's craft"}],["$","p","22",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] h-6","children":""}],["$","p","23",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"The Battle of Talas —"}],["$","p","24",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A military defeat"}],["$","p","25",{"className":"min-h-[1.5em] ","children":"A civilizational triumph"}]]}],false,["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-20 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex justify-between items-center text-sm text-gray-500 font-sans","children":[["$","span",null,{"children":["《","Blood-Sweating Horses",